This paper is about designing neural networks for video action recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithmic approaches for neural architecture search, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed approach, which is relevant to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category.
